<br>
I can tell you that at the top end of the game, Warriors are essential. Period, end of story. It is all because of Defensive. There are several pallies and a sk in our guild that have comparable ACs and slightly lower hps then myself , but they simply cannot tank mobs that hit for 900+ without the dmg reduction of Defensive. The clerics really cannot keep up the healing required on them, for a fight of any length. <br>
<br>
With the new abilities, melee can buy, it makes us even better. <br>
<br>
As for dmg output, sure rogues out damage us, thanks to Backstab. If I stand toe to toe with a rogue and hit auto attack, and he does the same, there is no question I will win. I think it is safe to say this would be true of any class we stood toe to toe with. When you throw in variables, that is where the strengths of other classes come out. (Backstabs for rogues, healing for pallies, damage spells/dots/FD for sk's, mend/fd/awesome dmg &lt;120% of a warrior?&gt; for monks, etc)  <br>
<br>
I guess what I am saying is warriors were overpowered in Velious. It was getting so bad that on every raid we would have 10+ warriors/clerics/rogues, and just a handful of the other classes. I am glad to see things being evened out a bit, as well as the diversity that comes with the different classes. <br>
<br>
<br>
Nazlug<br>
ED<br>
